1113
01:49:51,383 --> 01:49:53,543
So, I want you to talk a bit about that.

1114
01:49:53,583 --> 01:49:57,143
My reason for wanting
these characters to be from Angola,

1115
01:49:57,183 --> 01:50:01,103
as opposed to East Africa,
which is where I'm from,

1116
01:50:01,143 --> 01:50:03,423
is specifically because of the music

1117
01:50:03,463 --> 01:50:06,703
and the dance that goes with the music,
which I love,

1118
01:50:06,743 --> 01:50:09,703
and I'm a practitioner of Kizomba,

1119
01:50:09,743 --> 01:50:11,823
which is the style that Walter practises.

1120
01:50:15,263 --> 01:50:19,583
Kizomba is a very beautiful,
sensual couples dance from Angola,

1121
01:50:19,623 --> 01:50:22,463
which... ah... you know, most people

1122
01:50:22,503 --> 01:50:27,863
don't think beautiful, sensual
couples dance is from Africa, period.

1123
01:50:27,903 --> 01:50:30,783
You know, most African dance
is characterised by drumming

1124
01:50:30,823 --> 01:50:33,063
and the fertility dance,
or the rain dance,

1125
01:50:33,103 --> 01:50:36,623
or, you know, something like that,
which is great, we have those too.

1126
01:50:36,663 --> 01:50:38,583
But we also have these.

1127
01:50:41,103 --> 01:50:45,583
The thing about Kizomba,
which makes it very unique for me,

1128
01:50:45,623 --> 01:50:52,263
is that there is not
a regular foot pattern to the dance.

1129
01:50:52,303 --> 01:50:56,783
The leader is dancing to the music
and to how they feel about the music,

1130
01:50:56,823 --> 01:51:01,383
and your job, as the follower,
is to be connected to them

1131
01:51:01,423 --> 01:51:03,343
so that you can follow,

1132
01:51:03,383 --> 01:51:05,743
because they can change at any moment.

1133
01:51:05,783 --> 01:51:08,063
And, so, there is a level of connection
that's required.

1134
01:51:08,103 --> 01:51:10,543
It's a very close...
It looks like a really...

1135
01:51:10,583 --> 01:51:13,463
A lot of people get very intimidated
because it looks super sexy.

1136
01:51:13,503 --> 01:51:17,463
And it is but you actually have
to concentrate quite a bit,

1137
01:51:17,503 --> 01:51:20,423
because you really do need to, like,

1138
01:51:20,463 --> 01:51:25,543
have some sort of connection
with your partner in order to perform.

1139
01:51:25,583 --> 01:51:28,343
And I just thought
it was a really interesting metaphor

1140
01:51:28,383 --> 01:51:30,863
for a relationship of these two people

1141
01:51:30,903 --> 01:51:34,263
who were in sync,
literally, were in step,

1142
01:51:34,303 --> 01:51:37,303
and, because of distance,
because of time have fallen out of step

1143
01:51:37,343 --> 01:51:40,103
and are therefore
not able to dance together.

1144
01:51:48,623 --> 01:51:51,663
Kuduro, which is the style
that Sylvia practises,

1145
01:51:51,703 --> 01:51:53,743
is also out of Angola.

1146
01:51:53,783 --> 01:51:56,783
It's kind of harsh and from the streets
and from the youth and,

1147
01:51:56,823 --> 01:52:00,223
you know, young people,
it's their way of expressing the things

1148
01:52:00,263 --> 01:52:02,263
that they can't say to their elders.

1149
01:52:02,303 --> 01:52:05,183
You know, their frustrations
with the economic situation

1150
01:52:05,223 --> 01:52:08,383
or, you know,
coming out of a 30-year civil war

1151
01:52:08,423 --> 01:52:12,183
and what that's done to the country
and to people and domestic violence

1152
01:52:12,223 --> 01:52:14,303
and all these different topics
that people,

1153
01:52:14,343 --> 01:52:18,863
you know, have feelings about it,
but don't have a place to express it,

1154
01:52:18,903 --> 01:52:21,143
other than through their dance
and their music.

1155
01:52:21,183 --> 01:52:24,143
Watch her closely. She's the one to beat.

1156
01:52:24,183 --> 01:52:28,383
For Sylvia, as a young African girl,

1157
01:52:28,423 --> 01:52:32,903
who is not raised
to speak back to her parents

1158
01:52:32,943 --> 01:52:35,503
and tell them off - you know,
that would never happen -

1159
01:52:35,543 --> 01:52:38,623
this would be the only way
that she would be able to express herself.

1160
01:52:38,663 --> 01:52:41,623
I loved one other quality about the music,

1161
01:52:41,663 --> 01:52:47,863
as Walter says at one point, you know,
it's the vehicle of freedom.

1162
01:52:47,903 --> 01:52:48,903
Mm-hm, yeah.

1163
01:52:48,943 --> 01:52:51,783
Dancing to music,
you set yourself free.

1164
01:52:51,823 --> 01:52:55,103
But it's also the way in which...

1165
01:52:55,143 --> 01:52:59,905
